        public CustomDate getDateFromString​(java.lang.String input)
                             throws TigerDateParsingException
        Takes in a string representation of the date and converts it to a CustomDate object. If an input day is not given, the function assumes it to be today.
        Parameters:
        input - String Represention of Date.
        Returns:
        The corresponding CustomDate object.
        Throws:
        TigerDateParsingException - if the date is not in the format specified.
